                        <interp inst="t18770108-name-176" type="given" value="THEODORE"></interp>THEODORE WAGNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am employed by Messrs. Candy &amp;Co., of 4 and 5, Watling Street—on 11th September, the prisoner brought this letter (<hi rend="italic">This letter was signed "Henry Smith" and addressed to Messrs. Candy &amp;Co., and stating that nothing should be left undone to make their relations satisfac<lb></lb>tory.</hi>) The prisoner waited to see my partner, Mr. Candy, but I asked if he was Henry Smith's assistant; he said "Yes"—I introduced him to our salesman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> Nothing passed as to terms—it was not my department.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18770108-name-177" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18770108-name-177" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
